			<Text>The tipi (or teepee) is a portable, conical tent constructed of tanned hides and wooden poles traditionally associated with the migratory North American Plains Indians. The word itself comes from the Lakota for "they dwell." Often elaborately painted, tipis served to identify the separate tribes.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Yields 1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and 1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture, and another [ICON_CULTURE] Culture after researching Archaeology. They may only be built on flat Plains tiles, and not next to another Tipi. May be built within Forest tiles, but removes Jungle tiles.</Text>
